comments: Smart (BOS) goes through Green's (GSW) space during the pick and the contact dislodges him from his obtained position.
Tatum (BOS) briefly places his hands on Green (GSW) in the post, but the contact is marginal.
Thompson (GSW) briefly grasps Horford's (BOS) arm moving towards the lane and marginal contact occurs as Thompson immediately slides his hand off as he gathers the pass.
Wiggins (GSW) places his forearm to Tatum's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs defending his drive to the basket.
Brogdon (BOS) goes to, not through, Green's (GSW) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the pick.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Brogdon's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact.
Horford (BOS) places his forearm to Poole's (GSW) side and slides his arm off defending his drive to the basket.
Horford (BOS) cleanly blocks Poole's (GSW) driving shot attempt before incidental body contact occurs.
Wiggins (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Tatum (BOS) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Tatum (BOS) reaches in and makes contact with the ball when Green (GSW) recovers the loose ball.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Smart's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Curry (GSW) lowers his arm and makes contact with the ball and marginal contact occurs as Tatum (BOS) leans into him to attempt to make the pass.
Smart (BOS) briefly places his hand to Curry's (GSW) side and then loses his balance on his own as he moves behind him.
Tatum (BOS) jumps alongside Curry's (GSW) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) briefly places his hands on Green (GSW) prior to switching onto Curry (GSW).
Horford (BOS) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) arm after the release.
Smart (BOS) and Green (GSW) mutually engage and immediately disengage during the rebound.

A timeout is granted to Boston and the game clock expires.  After communicating with the Replay Center, it is determined that Boston signals for a timeout with 0.5 seconds remaining and the game clock is reset to 00:00.5.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Brown (BOS) grasps and then quickly releases Green's (GSW) jersey off-ball.
Horford (BOS) is moving alongside Curry's (GSW) path and marginal body contact occurs during Curry's (GSW) drive.
Green (GSW) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Brogdon (BOS) and incidental contact occurs as Brogdon (BOS) attempts to move over the screen.
Tatum (BOS) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Brogdon (BOS) initiates contact with Poole's (GSW) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Smart (BOS) and Wiggins (GSW) come together in transition off ball and marginal contact occurs as they absorb each others contact.
Poole (GSW) places his hand to Brown's (BOS) arm at the start of his drive before correcting.
Poole (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Brown (BOS) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
After the ball becomes loose, Brown (BOS) and Poole (GSW) both engage with one another in pursuit of the loose ball.
Horford (BOS) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Green (GSW) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Tatum's (BOS) arm after the release.
Tatum (BOS) places his forearm to Curry's (GSW) front as he hedges the pick and marginal body contact occurs defending his drive to the basket.
Brown (BOS) initiates contact with Curry's (GSW) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) establishes himself in Wiggins's (GSW) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Wiggins (GSW) places his forearm to Tatum's (BOS) side and marginal body contact occurs as he defends over the pick.
Smart (BOS) establishes himself in Wiggins's (GSW) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Thompson (GSW) reaches down and makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with Brown's (BOS) hand on the ball.
Wiggins (GSW) establishes himself in Tatum's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Green (GSW) hands off the ball in Smart's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Tatum (BOS) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) arm after the release.
Curry (GSW) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Brogdon (BOS) goes to, not through, Poole's (GSW) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together off-ball.
DiVincenzo (GSW) and Brown (BOS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Smart (BOS) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with DiVincenzo (GSW) and incidental contact occurs as DiVincenzo (GSW) attempts to move over the screen.
Wiggins (GSW) initiates contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) briefly has a hand placed on Green's (GSW) back as the two players engage and disengage.
Smart (BOS) and Curry (GSW) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Poole (GSW) stops short and begins to lose his balance prior to the marginal contact with Brogdon (BOS).

Replay review of the foul called on Horford (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Horford (BOS) initiates contact to Wiggins' (GSW) arm during his upward shooting motion and the contact affects his jump shot attempt.
Brogdon (BOS) is moving alongside Poole's (GSW) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Smart's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact.
Brogdon (BOS) engages with DiVincenzo (GSW) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Brogdon (BOS) releases away to defend the entry pass.
Wiggins (GSW) and Brogdon (BOS) come together in transition and incidental foot to foot contact occurs.
Brown (BOS) remains in bounds before making contact with the ball.
Wiggins (GSW) briefly places his hand to Tatum's (BOS) front in transition before correcting.
Brown (BOS) establishes himself in Wiggins's (GSW) path and makes marginal contact to Wiggins' side as they disengage.
The ball is still in Horford's (BOS) possession when the shot clock expires.
Green (GSW) jumps alongside Horford's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) brings his off-arm outward and marginal contact occurs with Green (GSW) during the driving shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) jumps along Wiggins' (GSW) side and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Wiggins (GSW) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and Boston should have retained possession.
